ook provides information for Computer Science and Engineering students at Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife. It covers departmental staff, university history, facilities, examination regulations, the degree program, and procedures for academic matters.  The handbook aims to guide students through their studies and advises them to consult their academic advisors for major decisions.", "source": {"organization": "Obafemi Awolowo University", "url": null, "authority_tier": 3, "reliability_score": 0.9}, "temporal": {"publication_date": "2008", "last_updated": "August 2014", "validity_period": "2008", "version": null}, "classification": {"education_level": ["tertiary"], "content_type": "handbook", "subject_areas": ["Computer Science", "Engineering", "Mathematics", "Economics"], "geographic_scope": "institutional", "institution_types": ["university"]}, "processing": {"extraction_method": "manual", "quality_score": 0.9, "human_verified": false, "last_reviewed": null, "last_modified": null}, "linguistic": {"primary_language": "english", "secondary_languages": [], "terminology_complexity": "intermediate"}, "search_optimization": {"keywords": ["Obafemi Awolowo University", "Ile-Ife", "Computer Science", "Engineering", "Handbook", "Students", "Undergraduate", "Postgraduate", "Degree Program", "Examination Regulations"], "synonyms": [], "common_queries": ["What are the admission requirements?", "What courses are offered?", "What are the examination rules?", "Who are the departmental staff?", "What are the university facilities?"]}}, "document_id": "9af9d4ac-bfd1-420d-b3cf-de2fa40f2758"}, "hash": "e3ca53226b1703ff46ef9c1278f3f161435702453edf406e0be57f58c704312a", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "You will need a sick letter to cover the period of your absence due to illness. It is important  \nto document any health problem that you may have during any academic period because  \nyour course lecturer and any other person or body may demand for it. Please note that the  \nonly valid medical report is that issued by the Health Center of the Obafemi Awolowo  \nUniversity. Thus any medical report you bring from home must first be lodged at the  \nHealth Center for validation. The production of a valid medical report can save you from a  \nnumber of problems.\nDo not run away from school and do not deceive your Part Academic Adviser, parents, or  \nteachers. You will not gain anything good by so doing. The Department, and indeed the  \nUniversity, may not be able to assist any student who foments trouble outside the university \ncampus.  You are therefore strongly advised to stay out of  trouble  or any conflict  \nwithin/outside the university campus . Students leaving in rented apartments outside the  \nuniversity campus are particularly warned to be very careful. University regulations may  \nnot be applicable outside the university campus nor do they operate on private property.\nIn the past some students have reported problems with different degree of complexities.  \nEach candidate\u2019s problem will be handled based on the merit and situation of the case. The  \ntable below shows some problems and how it has been handled in the past.\nProblem Suggested Solution\nCourse See the lecturer or coordinator of the course\nResult See the lecturer or coordinator of the course\nAccommodation/problem \nwith roommate\nSee the Hall wardens and Hall executive if need be.\nTime table See your Departmental Time Table Coordinator\nPersonal See your Part Academic Adviser\nStudents Association See your association officials, if this fails see your  \nHead of Department\nScholarship Go to Directorate of students affairs\nAcademic performance. See your Part Academic Adviser\nLetters of recommendation See your Part Academic Adviser\nLeave/Leave of Absence See your Part Academic Adviser\nGeneral problem See your Part Academic Adviser\nIn most cases your Part Academic Adviser may not be able to help you when you have  \nfinancial problems. This suggests that you must be prudent with money and other resources  \ngiven to you from home.  \nA number of cases have been reported to the Department in which some students are  \ninvolved in physical confrontation with other students with whom they share rooms. You  \nare advised, to live in peace with your roommates. You may loose your accommodation or  \neven your studentship, if you engage in frequent fights in halls of residence.\n(f) Students with Special Physical Condition  \nSound mental health is a precondition for admission into a Degree programme in Obafemi  \nAwolowo  University.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 13479, "end_char_idx": 16302, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "8f9368f4-3fa4-46c1-a0cf-4b1d3e9bc46e": {"__data__": {"id_": "8f9368f4-3fa4-46c1-a0cf-4b1d3e9bc46e", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "1", "file_name": "undergradute_handbook.pdf", "file_path": "data/undergradute_handbook.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 423047, "creation_date": "2025-07-23", "last_modified_date": "2025-07-23", "source_type": "file", "page_count": 31, "edubot_metadata": {"document_id": "9af9d4ac-bfd1-420d-b3cf-de2fa40f2758", "date_uploaded": "2025-07-31T01:10:20.972861", "title": "2008 Handbook", "summary": "This handbook provides information for Computer Science and Engineering students at Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife. It covers departmental staff, university history, facilities, examination regulations, the degree program, and procedures for academic matters.  The handbook aims to guide students through their studies and advises them to consult their academic advisors for major decisions.", "source": {"organization": "Obafemi Awolowo University", "url": null, "authority_tier": 3, "reliability_score": 0.9}, "temporal": {"publication_date": "2008", "last_updated": "Augu