 their studies and advises them to consult their academic advisors for major decisions.", "source": {"organization": "Obafemi Awolowo University", "url": null, "authority_tier": 3, "reliability_score": 0.9}, "temporal": {"publication_date": "2008", "last_updated": "August 2014", "validity_period": "2008", "version": null}, "classification": {"education_level": ["tertiary"], "content_type": "handbook", "subject_areas": ["Computer Science", "Engineering", "Mathematics", "Economics"], "geographic_scope": "institutional", "institution_types": ["university"]}, "processing": {"extraction_method": "manual", "quality_score": 0.9, "human_verified": false, "last_reviewed": null, "last_modified": null}, "linguistic": {"primary_language": "english", "secondary_languages": [], "terminology_complexity": "intermediate"}, "search_optimization": {"keywords": ["Obafemi Awolowo University", "Ile-Ife", "Computer Science", "Engineering", "Handbook", "Students", "Undergraduate", "Postgraduate", "Degree Program", "Examination Regulations"], "synonyms": [], "common_queries": ["What are the admission requirements?", "What courses are offered?", "What are the examination rules?", "Who are the departmental staff?", "What are the university facilities?"]}}, "document_id": "9af9d4ac-bfd1-420d-b3cf-de2fa40f2758"}, "hash": "8ff5022272fe24edb9c7a64b498ebfbaa5253af1f9b69ea4c392822ea243cfdf", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "4": {"node_id": "6d6b012b-745d-4abc-b46d-40386b28cbdc", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "1", "file_name": "undergradute_handbook.pdf", "file_path": "data/undergradute_handbook.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 423047, "creation_date": "2025-07-23", "last_modified_date": "2025-07-23", "source_type": "file", "page_count": 31, "edubot_metadata": {"document_id": "9af9d4ac-bfd1-420d-b3cf-de2fa40f2758", "date_uploaded": "2025-07-31T01:10:20.972861", "title": "2008 Handbook", "summary": "This handbook provides information for Computer Science and Engineering students at Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife. It covers departmental staff, university history, facilities, examination regulations, the degree program, and procedures for academic matters.  The handbook aims to guide students through their studies and advises them to consult their academic advisors for major decisions.", "source": {"organization": "Obafemi Awolowo University", "url": null, "authority_tier": 3, "reliability_score": 0.9}, "temporal": {"publication_date": "2008", "last_updated": "August 2014", "validity_period": "2008", "version": null}, "classification": {"education_level": ["tertiary"], "content_type": "handbook", "subject_areas": ["Computer Science", "Engineering", "Mathematics", "Economics"], "geographic_scope": "institutional", "institution_types": ["university"]}, "processing": {"extraction_method": "manual", "quality_score": 0.9, "human_verified": false, "last_reviewed": null, "last_modified": null}, "linguistic": {"primary_language": "english", "secondary_languages": [], "terminology_complexity": "intermediate"}, "search_optimization": {"keywords": ["Obafemi Awolowo University", "Ile-Ife", "Computer Science", "Engineering", "Handbook", "Students", "Undergraduate", "Postgraduate", "Degree Program", "Examination Regulations"], "synonyms": [], "common_queries": ["What are the admission requirements?", "What courses are offered?", "What are the examination rules?", "Who are the departmental staff?", "What are the university facilities?"]}}, "document_id": "9af9d4ac-bfd1-420d-b3cf-de2fa40f2758"}, "hash": "776f6b9fb0e62b865d46c69f51329fa39a9559a073bac70b46b6808bbf66c0f4", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "However,  students  with  specific  physical  condition  have  been \nadmitted  into  the  University  for  various  degree  programmes.  A  number  of  physically \nimpaired students have graduated from Computer Science & Engineering Department and  \nsome are currently registered as full time students in the Department. It is important to note  \nthat most of these students have performed excellently well. \nIf  you  have  any  physical  disabilities,  it  is  important  that  you  give  the  Health  Center \nadequate information about your situation, including your drugs, special therapies, etc.  \nThereafter, you should inform your Part Academic Adviser, who will guide and advice you  \non how to cope within the university environment. Asthmatic students are particularly  \nadvised to inform the Department of their situation and make sure they have their inhaler  \nwith them at all times.  If you use any special equipment, such as Wheel Chair or crushes,  \nyou must ensure that they are in very good condition at all times. If your physical condition  \npermits such, a helper will be allowed to stay with you in the halls of residence.  Some  \nHall/rooms, are specially allocated to handicapped students, you are therefore advised to  \nrequest for an accommodation that will not hinder or delay your access to academic areas.\nIn  the  event  that  you  have  problem  accessing  lecture  hall,  practical  classes,  test  or \nexamination venue, please lodge a written complain to the lecturer of the course and submit \na copy of such complain to your Part Academic Adviser. The written compliant should  \nreach the appropriate official at least two weeks before the expected activity. \nIn some situation lecture venue may be changed to favour handicapped students. This may  \nnot be possible in many other situations. If you find it difficult getting to lecture venue,  \nplease contact the lecturer of the course. In the meantime, however, collect lecture notes  \nfrom your colleagues in order to make sure you have up-to-date lecture notes. \nBlind students will require tape recorder and cassettes to take lectures as well as typewriters \nto  write  test  and  examination.  Brail  textbooks  are  also  necessary.  At  present  the \nDepartment does not have special arrangement or provision for this type of facility. Blind  \nstudents are therefore advice to make arrangement for all necessary materials. \nLeft-handed students and students who are short sighted may locate their sit in the front  \nrow and side walks of lecture halls.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 2544, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "170d5ca7-032d-47c3-a926-9f158e4d5b73": {"__data__": {"id_": "170d5ca7-032d-47c3-a926-9f158e4d5b73", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "1", "file_name": "undergradute_handbook.pdf", "file_path": "data/undergradute_handbook.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 423047, "creation_date": "2025-07-23", "last_modified_date": "2025-07-23", "source_type": "file", "page_count": 31, "edubot_metadata": {"document_id": "9af9d4ac-bfd1-420d-b3cf-de2fa40f2758", "date_uploaded": "2025-07-31T01:10:20.972861", "title": "2008 Handbook", "summary": "This handbook provides information for Computer Science and Engineering students at Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife. It covers departmental staff, university history, facilities, examination regulations, the degree program, and procedures for academic matters.  The handbook aims to guide students through their studies and advises them to consult their academic advisors for major decisions.", "source": {"organization": "Obafemi Awolowo University", "url": null, "authority_tier": 3, "reliability_score": 0.9}, "temporal": {"publication_date": "2008", "last_updated": "August 2014", "validity_period": "2008", "version": null}, "classification": {"education_level": ["tertiary"], "content_type": "handbook", "subject_areas": ["Computer Science", "Engineering", "Mathematics", "Economics"], "geographic_scope": "institutional", "institution_types": ["university"]}, "processing": {"extraction_method": "manual", "quality_score": 0.9,