-07-31T01:10:20.972861", "title": "2008 Handbook", "summary": "This handbook provides information for Computer Science and Engineering students at Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife. It covers departmental staff, university history, facilities, examination regulations, the degree program, and procedures for academic matters.  The handbook aims to guide students through their studies and advises them to consult their academic advisors for major decisions.", "source": {"organization": "Obafemi Awolowo University", "url": null, "authority_tier": 3, "reliability_score": 0.9}, "temporal": {"publication_date": "2008", "last_updated": "August 2014", "validity_period": "2008", "version": null}, "classification": {"education_level": ["tertiary"], "content_type": "handbook", "subject_areas": ["Computer Science", "Engineering", "Mathematics", "Economics"], "geographic_scope": "institutional", "institution_types": ["university"]}, "processing": {"extraction_method": "manual", "quality_score": 0.9, "human_verified": false, "last_reviewed": null, "last_modified": null}, "linguistic": {"primary_language": "english", "secondary_languages": [], "terminology_complexity": "intermediate"}, "search_optimization": {"keywords": ["Obafemi Awolowo University", "Ile-Ife", "Computer Science", "Engineering", "Handbook", "Students", "Undergraduate", "Postgraduate", "Degree Program", "Examination Regulations"], "synonyms": [], "common_queries": ["What are the admission requirements?", "What courses are offered?", "What are the examination rules?", "Who are the departmental staff?", "What are the university facilities?"]}}, "document_id": "9af9d4ac-bfd1-420d-b3cf-de2fa40f2758"}, "hash": "d933fc45506ac734a8fd41c2a518bf68ab50f9844152ae4b2e49ca35fa311e15", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "b. University  examiners  in  each  of  the  department  within  the  faculty  shall  be \nappointed  annually  by  the  Business  Committee  on  behalf  of  Senate  on  the \nrecommendation  of  the  faculty  board  from  among  the  academic  staff  of  the \nuniversity.  An  Assistant  Lecturer shall not normally be appointed an  Examiner. \nOne  of  the  University  Examiners  normally  the  Head  of  Department  shall  be \ndesignated Chief Examiner.\nc. All  appointment  of  University  Examiners  shall  normally  be  made  at  the  first \nmeeting of the Business Committee of Senate of each academic year, provided that  \nsubsequent  additional  appointments  may  be  processed  to  the  senate  as \nrecommended by the Faculty Board.\nd. In the event of an emergency, the Vice-Chancellor may on the recommendation of  \nthe appropriate Deans of a Faculty, appoint an Examiners to fill a vacancy provided \nalways that such action is reported to the next Senate meeting for ratification.\n\uf0a7 Functions of Examiners\nI.       The Chief Examiner\no He shall be responsible for collection, collation and harmonization of all the  \nsegments of a paper/or a course examination.\no He shall ensure  that  all  the  questions  are coordinated and enough copies \nduplicated for each course.\no He shall arrange for the marking and presentation of the results through the  \nappropriate channels to senate in good time.\nII. External Examiner\no No person who has been involved in teaching a particular subject during an  \nacademic session shall be appointed an external examiner for that session.\no It shall be the duty of the External Examiner where applicable, to assist in the  \nconduct of the examination for which he/she been appointed and in particular:\n\uf0d8 to scrutinize draft question papers and to satisfy himself that  \nthe questions are appropriate, having regard to the approved syllabus for  \nthe  course being examined  and the  level  of the  examination,  and  to \nrecommend such alternation or modifications to the papers as he may  \nthink  desirable;  all  question  papers  must  be  signed  by  the  external \nexaminer;\n\uf0d8 to mark or revise the marking of scripts in consultation with the \nChief Examiner in the subject;\n\uf0d8 to assess practical or oral tests in consultation with the  Chief \nExaminer in the subject;\n\uf0d8 to participate in the determination of result and to adjudicate in  \ncases of disagreement among University Examiners in consultation with  \nthe Chief Examiner;\n\uf0d8 to submit to the Vice-chancellor on  the  completion of each  \nexamination, a confidential report on the examination in the subject with  \nparticular reference to the following points;\n\uf0a7 the general standard of the examination and the performance of the  \ncandidates;\n\uf0a7 the standard of marking by the University Examiners;\n\uf0a7 a  critical  appraisal  of  the  conduct  of  the  examination,  with \nsuggestion for improvement on future occasions.\nQuestion Papers\na. Question papers for the Harmattan Semester and Rain Semester shall be  \nset at the appropriate time.  All question papers shall be signed by the  \nChief  Examiner/Coordinator  and  at  least  one  of  the  University \nExaminers concerned and where there is an  External  Examiner, by the  \nExternal Examiners as well.\nb. Examiners must make available to the Head of Department exact sources \nof any copyrighted materials used in the question papers set by them.\nc. The question paper must be written legibly or typed personally by the  \nexaminer himself under confidential cover to the Chief Examiner.\nd. The course number and titles of paper in each subject must conform with  \nthe numbers and titles in the university handbook.\n\ne. The  chief  Examiner  in  each  subject  shall  be  responsible  for  the \ncorrections of the question papers.  All corrected proofs must be signed  \nby the Chief Examiner or one of the University Examiners.\nf. Map, drawings, photographs, sketches and any other materials needed  \nfor reproduction in question papers must be sent in a form which can be  \nreproduced without modification and must be submitted along with the  \nquestion papers.\ng. All examiners are required to strictly preserve the secrecy of question  \npapers at all stages until after examination.  The content of question  \npaper must not be disclosed to any person other than fellow examiners in  \nthe same subject or any person legitimately allowed having access to it.\n\uf0a7    Answer Script\na. The Chief Examiner shall arrange for delivery of marked answer scripts  \nto  External  Examiners where applicable.  On  on  condition should the  \nscripts  be  forwarded  by  post  or  sent  abroad  except  in  exceptional \ncircumstances and with the express permission of the Vice-Chancellor.\nb. The authorized assessment procedure for university examination is that  \napproved by senate and it is the duty of the course examiner to ensure  \nthat this scheme is strictly adhered to.\nc. On the completion of the examinations, answer scripts shall be retained  \nby the  Head of  Department for at least three years after the date of  \nexamination after which they may be destroyed.\n\uf0a7 Faculty Board of Examiners\na. Membership\nThe Board of Examiners of a faculty shall be constituted as follows:\no The Dean of the faculty as chairperson,\no The Heads of Department and all other University approved Examiners in  \nthe faculty;\no Where applicable the relevant External Examiner\nb. Functions\nThe function of the Board of Examiners of a Faculty shall be:\nto consider and ratify the marks, and in final examinations, the classifications  \nrecommended by departmental board of examiners in respect of graduating  \nstudents;\nto make recommendations to the Faculty Board for the award of degree, diplomas \nand certificates;\nto consider all cases of absence or withdrawal from examinations and to make  \nrecommendations to the Faculty Board;\nto make recommendations to the Faculty Board for the award of distinctions and  \nprizes.\n\uf0a7 Departmental Board of Examiners\na. Membership\nThe Departmental Board of Examiners shall be constituted as follows:\nThe Chief Examiner (chairperson)\nThe External Examiner(s) where applicable as well as all University Examiners  \nin each paper.\nb. Functions\nThe functions of the departmental board of examiners shall be:\nthe moderation of all examination questions;\nto consider the marks awarded to candidates for individual courses;\nto make recommendations to the Faculty Board of Examiners.\nPattern of examination and Assessment under the Course Unit System\n1. PATTERN OF EXAMINATION\n(i) Each course shall be examined at the end of the course.  The  \nexamination shall be conducted as prescribed by Senate.\n(ii) Each examination shall be 1-3 hours in duration.  In addition there \nmay be a practical paper and/or an oral examination.\n(iii) There shall be continuous assessment of each course and this shall \nconstitute a percentage of the final grade.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 6811, "end_char_idx": 13727, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "e4d49c47-6491-454b-af2d-a48fd662dc18": {"__data__": {"id_": "e4d49c47-6491-454b-af2d-a48fd662dc18", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "1", "file_name": "undergradute_handbook.pdf", "file_path": "data/undergradute_handbook.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 423047, "creation_date": "2025-07-23", "last_modified_date": "2025-07-23", "source_type": "file", "page_count": 31, "edubot_metadata": {"document_id": "9af9d4ac-bfd1-420d-b3cf-de2fa40f2758", "date_uploaded": "2025-07-31T01:10:20.972861", "title": "2008 Handbook", "summary": "This handbook provides information for Computer Science and Engineering students at Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife. It covers departmental staff, university history, facilities, examination regulations, the degree program, and procedures for academic matters.  The handbook aim