dbook aims to guide students through their studies and advises them to consult their academic advisors for major decisions.", "source": {"organization": "Obafemi Awolowo University", "url": null, "authority_tier": 3, "reliability_score": 0.9}, "temporal": {"publication_date": "2008", "last_updated": "August 2014", "validity_period": "2008", "version": null}, "classification": {"education_level": ["tertiary"], "content_type": "handbook", "subject_areas": ["Computer Science", "Engineering", "Mathematics", "Economics"], "geographic_scope": "institutional", "institution_types": ["university"]}, "processing": {"extraction_method": "manual", "quality_score": 0.9, "human_verified": false, "last_reviewed": null, "last_modified": null}, "linguistic": {"primary_language": "english", "secondary_languages": [], "terminology_complexity": "intermediate"}, "search_optimization": {"keywords": ["Obafemi Awolowo University", "Ile-Ife", "Computer Science", "Engineering", "Handbook", "Students", "Undergraduate", "Postgraduate", "Degree Program", "Examination Regulations"], "synonyms": [], "common_queries": ["What are the admission requirements?", "What courses are offered?", "What are the examination rules?", "Who are the departmental staff?", "What are the university facilities?"]}}, "document_id": "9af9d4ac-bfd1-420d-b3cf-de2fa40f2758"}, "hash": "8ff5022272fe24edb9c7a64b498ebfbaa5253af1f9b69ea4c392822ea243cfdf", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "4": {"node_id": "06fc71a4-0e7d-451b-a10e-2cc6fc6b9a7b", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "1", "file_name": "undergradute_handbook.pdf", "file_path": "data/undergradute_handbook.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 423047, "creation_date": "2025-07-23", "last_modified_date": "2025-07-23", "source_type": "file", "page_count": 31, "edubot_metadata": {"document_id": "9af9d4ac-bfd1-420d-b3cf-de2fa40f2758", "date_uploaded": "2025-07-31T01:10:20.972861", "title": "2008 Handbook", "summary": "This handbook provides information for Computer Science and Engineering students at Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife. It covers departmental staff, university history, facilities, examination regulations, the degree program, and procedures for academic matters.  The handbook aims to guide students through their studies and advises them to consult their academic advisors for major decisions.", "source": {"organization": "Obafemi Awolowo University", "url": null, "authority_tier": 3, "reliability_score": 0.9}, "temporal": {"publication_date": "2008", "last_updated": "August 2014", "validity_period": "2008", "version": null}, "classification": {"education_level": ["tertiary"], "content_type": "handbook", "subject_areas": ["Computer Science", "Engineering", "Mathematics", "Economics"], "geographic_scope": "institutional", "institution_types": ["university"]}, "processing": {"extraction_method": "manual", "quality_score": 0.9, "human_verified": false, "last_reviewed": null, "last_modified": null}, "linguistic": {"primary_language": "english", "secondary_languages": [], "terminology_complexity": "intermediate"}, "search_optimization": {"keywords": ["Obafemi Awolowo University", "Ile-Ife", "Computer Science", "Engineering", "Handbook", "Students", "Undergraduate", "Postgraduate", "Degree Program", "Examination Regulations"], "synonyms": [], "common_queries": ["What are the admission requirements?", "What courses are offered?", "What are the examination rules?", "Who are the departmental staff?", "What are the university facilities?"]}}, "document_id": "9af9d4ac-bfd1-420d-b3cf-de2fa40f2758"}, "hash": "c28a55c1d6c965d60a8abceae4f3544ee1b92ee4e4878f19496566f4b7aac94e", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "One semester  \n(Harmattan or Rain) is made up of approximately 15 weeks. A course also has a course  \ncode, title and a status. The course code is a three-character string, which identifies the  \nDepartment where it is serviced, and a three-digit course number. The semester as well as  \nthe level at which the course is offered can be read from the last three digits of a course  \ncode. Odd number coded courses are Harmattan (H) semester courses while even number  \ncodes are Rain (R) semester courses. The course title is a short description of the course.  \nFor example  CSC 301  is a course offered in the Department of Computer Science &  \nEngineering (CSC). It is a 300 level course that is offered in Harmattan semester only. The  \ntitle of the course is Low Level Languages.\nNote that Special Elective courses are not used to compute your final results but you have \nto pass them before you graduate . (Minimum of 12 units special elective courses are  \nrequired before graduation).\n\uf0a7 Calculating your Performance: To calculate your result, you need to understand the  \nfollowing abbreviated terms:\nTerms Meaning Explanation\nGPA Grade Point \nAverage\nThis is a real number (accurate to two decimal places) which  \nindicates  how  well  you  have  performed  in  one  academic \nTerms Meaning Explanation\nsemester. As an illustration, a student with GPA of 4.20 in  \none semester can be said to have scored 4.20 points out of 5  \npossible points or (4.20/5.00) in that semester only.\nCGPA Cumulative Grade \nPoint Average\nThis  is  a  number  (accurate  to  two  decimal  places)  which \nindicates your overall performance. It is usually rated over  \nfive. As an illustration, a Part IV student with CGPA of 4.2  \ncan be said to have scored 4.2 points out of 5 possible points  \naccumulated from Part I.\nTNU Total Number of \nUnits\nThis is the number of units (including special electives) you  \nregistered for in one semester.\nCTNU Cumulative Total \nNumber of Units\nThis is the total number of units (including special electives)  \nyou have registered for so far in your course.\nTOS Termination of \nStudentship\nStudentship  terminated;  student  is  advised  to  leave  the \ninstitution.  This  may  occur  if  you  fail to register for two \nconsecutive  semesters  without  acceptable  and  documented \nreasons.\nPROB Probation Student on academic probation. This will happen if a student  \nscores a CGPA less than 1.00 in any academic semester.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 2450, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "9be89397-ea99-4b1c-8479-5ab2133177b5": {"__data__": {"id_": "9be89397-ea99-4b1c-8479-5ab2133177b5", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "1", "file_name": "undergradute_handbook.pdf", "file_path": "data/undergradute_handbook.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 423047, "creation_date": "2025-07-23", "last_modified_date": "2025-07-23", "source_type": "file", "page_count": 31, "edubot_metadata": {"document_id": "9af9d4ac-bfd1-420d-b3cf-de2fa40f2758", "date_uploaded": "2025-07-31T01:10:20.972861", "title": "2008 Handbook", "summary": "This handbook provides information for Computer Science and Engineering students at Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife. It covers departmental staff, university history, facilities, examination regulations, the degree program, and procedures for academic matters.  The handbook aims to guide students through their studies and advises them to consult their academic advisors for major decisions.", "source": {"organization": "Obafemi Awolowo University", "url": null, "authority_tier": 3, "reliability_score": 0.9}, "temporal": {"publication_date": "2008", "last_updated": "August 2014", "validity_period": "2008", "version": null}, "classification": {"education_level": ["tertiary"], "content_type": "handbook", "subject_areas": ["Computer Science", "Engineering", "Mathematics", "Economics"], "geographic_scope": "institutional", "institution_types": ["university"]}, "processing": {"extraction_method": "manual", "quality_score": 0.9, "human_verified": false, "last_rev