.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 423047, "creation_date": "2025-07-23", "last_modified_date": "2025-07-23", "source_type": "file", "page_count": 31, "edubot_metadata": {"document_id": "9af9d4ac-bfd1-420d-b3cf-de2fa40f2758", "date_uploaded": "2025-07-31T01:10:20.972861", "title": "2008 Handbook", "summary": "This handbook provides information for Computer Science and Engineering students at Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife. It covers departmental staff, university history, facilities, examination regulations, the degree program, and procedures for academic matters.  The handbook aims to guide students through their studies and advises them to consult their academic advisors for major decisions.", "source": {"organization": "Obafemi Awolowo University", "url": null, "authority_tier": 3, "reliability_score": 0.9}, "temporal": {"publication_date": "2008", "last_updated": "August 2014", "validity_period": "2008", "version": null}, "classification": {"education_level": ["tertiary"], "content_type": "handbook", "subject_areas": ["Computer Science", "Engineering", "Mathematics", "Economics"], "geographic_scope": "institutional", "institution_types": ["university"]}, "processing": {"extraction_method": "manual", "quality_score": 0.9, "human_verified": false, "last_reviewed": null, "last_modified": null}, "linguistic": {"primary_language": "english", "secondary_languages": [], "terminology_complexity": "intermediate"}, "search_optimization": {"keywords": ["Obafemi Awolowo University", "Ile-Ife", "Computer Science", "Engineering", "Handbook", "Students", "Undergraduate", "Postgraduate", "Degree Program", "Examination Regulations"], "synonyms": [], "common_queries": ["What are the admission requirements?", "What courses are offered?", "What are the examination rules?", "Who are the departmental staff?", "What are the university facilities?"]}}, "document_id": "9af9d4ac-bfd1-420d-b3cf-de2fa40f2758"}, "hash": "048cd2af67bcddd4d6135fab7c992a6fb95b7f0a703031791553fe86e8bdbe36", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "At the end of each course the student submits a \ndetailed system report. The student gives one seminar on each problem solved. Different  \nseminar is organized with speakers from the Industry to intimate the students with Industry  \nrequirements and expectations. Also, postgraduate research works are presented to expose  \nstudents to possible research areas for future endeavours.\nCSC 507:  COMPUTERS IN SOCIETY (2 UNITS [2-0-0])\na) Introduction to the effects of the application of computers on social life: in education,  \nmedicine, business, science and research, etc. Effects on skills evaluation and employment.\nb) Social implications of networked communication (WWW).\nc) Growth of, control of, and access to the Internet and International issues\nd) Computer  usage  appropriate  for  education;  Promises  and  achievements  of  artificial \nintelligence;  the  computerized  society;  limitations  of  computers;  human  failures; \nProfessional responsibility.\ne) Computer crime; history and examples of computer crime \u201cCracking\u201d ( hacking) and its  \neffects. Viruses, worms, and Trojan horses Crime prevention strategies\nCSC 508:  COMPUTER SYSTEM PROJECT MANAGEMENT (2 UNITS [2-0-0])\na) Definition of computer project and project management.\nb) Components  and  features  of  a  good  computer  based  project  management  technique. \nComputer network administration.\nc) Function  of  members  and  team  management,  team  processes,  team  organization  and \ndecision-making,  roles  and  responsibilities  in  a  software  team,  role  identification  and \nassignment, team problem resolution.\nd) Project tracking\ne) Software Project scheduling, Budgeting and Planning; Project organization.\nf) Software measurement and estimation techniques, Risk analysis.\ng) Software quality assurance\nh) Software configuration management\ni) Project management tools\nCPE 509:  HARDWARE DESIGN LABORATORY (2 UNITS [0-0-6])\nStudents are expected to undertake a number of mini projects, designed to apply knowledge  \nin digital computer systems design and implementation.\nCPE 510: NATURAL LANGUAGE PROCESSING & APPLICATION (2 UNITS [2-0-0])\na) Deterministic  and  stochastic  grammars,  Parsing  algorithms,  Corpus-based  methods, \nInformation retrieval, Language translation.\nb) Fundamentals of natural language modeling (using a local language; Yoruba, Hausa, Igbo,  \nor any other African Language).\nc) Speech  recognition;  isolate,  connected  and  continuous  speech;  definition,  methods, \nproblems, examples; speaker recognition.\nd) Speech  synthesis;  articulatory,  format,  concatinative,  definition,  methods,  problems, \nexamples.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 2640, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "bd7765f4-0d00-443c-b827-a05cff31db98": {"__data__": {"id_": "bd7765f4-0d00-443c-b827-a05cff31db98", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "1", "file_name": "undergradute_handbook.pdf", "file_path": "data/undergradute_handbook.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 423047, "creation_date": "2025-07-23", "last_modified_date": "2025-07-23", "source_type": "file", "page_count": 31, "edubot_metadata": {"document_id": "9af9d4ac-bfd1-420d-b3cf-de2fa40f2758", "date_uploaded": "2025-07-31T01:10:20.972861", "title": "2008 Handbook", "summary": "This handbook provides information for Computer Science and Engineering students at Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife. It covers departmental staff, university history, facilities, examination regulations, the degree program, and procedures for academic matters.  The handbook aims to guide students through their studies and advises them to consult their academic advisors for major decisions.", "source": {"organization": 