bility_score": 0.9}, "temporal": {"publication_date": "2008", "last_updated": "August 2014", "validity_period": "2008", "version": null}, "classification": {"education_level": ["tertiary"], "content_type": "handbook", "subject_areas": ["Computer Science", "Engineering", "Mathematics", "Economics"], "geographic_scope": "institutional", "institution_types": ["university"]}, "processing": {"extraction_method": "manual", "quality_score": 0.9, "human_verified": false, "last_reviewed": null, "last_modified": null}, "linguistic": {"primary_language": "english", "secondary_languages": [], "terminology_complexity": "intermediate"}, "search_optimization": {"keywords": ["Obafemi Awolowo University", "Ile-Ife", "Computer Science", "Engineering", "Handbook", "Students", "Undergraduate", "Postgraduate", "Degree Program", "Examination Regulations"], "synonyms": [], "common_queries": ["What are the admission requirements?", "What courses are offered?", "What are the examination rules?", "Who are the departmental staff?", "What are the university facilities?"]}}, "document_id": "9af9d4ac-bfd1-420d-b3cf-de2fa40f2758"}, "hash": "a6525b1bbbfcabb3ed72c6ad30c8130e8997336e9039ae7859291191a5b4890a", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "4": {"node_id": "382181db-43ae-4043-9f59-a8b0755f378c", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "1", "file_name": "undergradute_handbook.pdf", "file_path": "data/undergradute_handbook.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 423047, "creation_date": "2025-07-23", "last_modified_date": "2025-07-23", "source_type": "file", "page_count": 31, "edubot_metadata": {"document_id": "9af9d4ac-bfd1-420d-b3cf-de2fa40f2758", "date_uploaded": "2025-07-31T01:10:20.972861", "title": "2008 Handbook", "summary": "This handbook provides information for Computer Science and Engineering students at Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife. It covers departmental staff, university history, facilities, examination regulations, the degree program, and procedures for academic matters.  The handbook aims to guide students through their studies and advises them to consult their academic advisors for major decisions.", "source": {"organization": "Obafemi Awolowo University", "url": null, "authority_tier": 3, "reliability_score": 0.9}, "temporal": {"publication_date": "2008", "last_updated": "August 2014", "validity_period": "2008", "version": null}, "classification": {"education_level": ["tertiary"], "content_type": "handbook", "subject_areas": ["Computer Science", "Engineering", "Mathematics", "Economics"], "geographic_scope": "institutional", "institution_types": ["university"]}, "processing": {"extraction_method": "manual", "quality_score": 0.9, "human_verified": false, "last_reviewed": null, "last_modified": null}, "linguistic": {"primary_language": "english", "secondary_languages": [], "terminology_complexity": "intermediate"}, "search_optimization": {"keywords": ["Obafemi Awolowo University", "Ile-Ife", "Computer Science", "Engineering", "Handbook", "Students", "Undergraduate", "Postgraduate", "Degree Program", "Examination Regulations"], "synonyms": [], "common_queries": ["What are the admission requirements?", "What courses are offered?", "What are the examination rules?", "Who are the departmental staff?", "What are the university facilities?"]}}, "document_id": "9af9d4ac-bfd1-420d-b3cf-de2fa40f2758"}, "hash": "b04027956daf87fc94cca900bf7f36f539ab9b2a25ee577a606212b80ff03dc1", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "Case studies using  \nSPSS or PSTAT or SAS packages. \nd) Software implementation of statistical algorithms.\ne) Interpretation of results.\n\nGuidelines for writing various applications on matters affecting students\u2019 academic work\nUniversity regulations make it mandatory for all students to formally apply for the consideration  \nof various matters affecting their academic work whenever such conditions arise. All applications for  \nthe consideration of such matters should be written to the Head of Department through Academic  \nAdvisers. The following are some of the conditions requiring formal applications: \n1. Application  for  Permission  to  Register  for  Less  Minimum  Number  of  Units   \n(application should be submitted during the normal registration period for the affected  \nsemester) \n2. Application  for  Leave  of  absence  for  the  current  semester   (application  should  be \nsubmitted during the normal registration period for the affected semester and not later than  \n2 weeks after the commencement of lectures)\n3. Notification  to Resume  Studies   (Any student  who has  enjoyed  Leave of  Absence  is \nrequired, on resumption of his studies, to so notify the University. Such notification should  \nbe submitted during the normal period of registration for the semester of resumption) \n4. Application  for  Deferment  of  SIWES   (Application  should  be  submitted  during  the \nnormal period of registration for the affected semester) \nFor each application, the application must provide relevant pieces of information as follows: \n1. Application for permission to Register for Less than Minimum Number of Units\n- Registration Number \n- Full name (surname first) \n- Part \n- List of course being registered for, together with their units \n- Total number of units \n- Reason (e.g. only courses left to graduate, only outstanding course for the semester, etc.) \n- Affected semester and session\n- Date of application. \n2. Application for Leave of Absence (current semester) \n- Registration Number \n- Part \n- Full name (surname first) \n- Duration of Leave of Absence (semester and session) \n- Reason (includes ill-health, financial problem, Late Transfer/Registration/Admission, no \ncourse to offer, etc)\n- Date of application. \n3. Notification to Resume Studies \n- Registration Number \n- Full name (surname first)\n- Part \n- Reason for original leave (includes ill-health, financial problem, Late \nTransfer/Registration/Admission) \n- Data of Approval of Leave (semester and session) \n- Duration of Leave of Absence (number of semesters) \n- Date of application. \n4. Deferment of SIWES \n- Registration Number \n- Full name (surname first)\n- Part Reason \n- Affected semester and session \n- Date of application. \nDEPARTMENT OF COMPUTER SCIENCE & ENGINEERING \nRECOMMENDED PROCEDURE FOR PROCESSING STUDENTS\u2019 APPLICATION\n1. Student will write their applications and complete the Clearance From on the advice of  \ntheir Part Adviser. The Part Adviser will ensure that each application is sufficiently detailed \nto contain all required information. Each application should be accompanied by relevant  \ndocuments as necessary. The application should be addressed to the Head of Department  \nthrough the Part Adviser. \n2. The Part adviser, after endorsing the application, will within 24 hours (excepting weekends  \nand holidays), pass it on to the Departmental Secretary for further action by the Head of  \nDepartment.\n3. The application will be accompanied by an appropriate clearance form and forwarded to  \nthe Examination Processing Unit for comments \n4. The application, together with the comments of the Examination Processing Unit, will be  \nreturned to the Head of Department (within 24 hours, excepting weekends and holidays) for \nfurther action.\n5. After consideration by the Faculty Board, the office of the Head of Department will convey  \nthe outcome for each application to the affected student, Part Academic Adviser and  the  \nExamination Processing Unit for implementation.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 6185, "end_char_idx": 10185, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "f3163414-9cad-48e5-b89c-04ab931b8e29": {"__data__": {"id_": "f3163414-9cad-48e5-b89c-04ab931b8e29", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "1", "file_name": "unilag_2