irements for various departments within different faculties, including UTME requirements, direct entry requirements (JUPEB/A' Level, HND/OND, NCE, diplomas), and O'Level requirements.  Specific subject combinations are listed for each department.", "source": {"organization": "University of Lagos", "url": null, "authority_tier": 3, "reliability_score": 1.0}, "temporal": {"publication_date": null, "last_updated": null, "validity_period": "2024/2025", "version": null}, "classification": {"education_level": ["tertiary"], "content_type": "admission", "subject_areas": ["Arts", "Basic Medical Sciences", "Clinical Sciences", "Dental Sciences", "Education", "Engineering", "Environmental Sciences", "Law", "Management Sciences", "Pharmacy", "Science", "Social Sciences", "Theatre Arts", "Visual Arts", "Music", "English Language", "European Languages", "French", "Russian", "German", "History", "Strategic Studies", "Linguistics", "African and Asian Studies", "Igbo", "Yoruba", "Chinese", "Philosophy", "Christian Religious Studies"], "geographic_scope": "national", "institution_types": ["university"]}, "processing": {"extraction_method": "manual", "quality_score": 1.0, "human_verified": false, "last_reviewed": null, "last_modified": null}, "linguistic": {"primary_language": "english", "secondary_languages": ["Igbo", "Yoruba", "French", "German", "Russian", "Chinese"], "terminology_complexity": "intermediate"}, "search_optimization": {"keywords": ["University of Lagos", "Admission", "Requirements", "2024", "2025", "UTME", "Direct Entry", "O'Level", "JUPEB", "A'Level", "HND", "OND", "NCE", "Diploma"], "synonyms": [], "common_queries": ["What are the admission requirements for University of Lagos?", "What are the UTME requirements for University of Lagos?", "What are the direct entry requirements for University of Lagos?", "What O'Level subjects are required for admission to University of Lagos?"]}}, "document_id": "90c4e014-c64f-45fd-94b1-92c468f2367c"}, "hash": "c796755cda9b452bdd2c5bb45c6435a418c7087e716ad884aade2c19a71071da", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "English Language, History and/or \nGovernment and any one or two \nArts or Social Sciences. \nLINGUISTICS, \nAFRICAN AND \nASIAN STUDIES \n\uf0b7 LINGUISTICS/ \nIGBO \n \n \ni. Very good passes in three JUPEB/A\u2019 Level \nsubjects in Igbo/Yoruba and any two of History, \nCRS/IRS, French, Government, Music, Visual \nArts and Literature-in-English. \nii. NCE (Merit) in two subjects to include a Nigerian \nLanguage.  \niii. LASU Diploma in Communication Arts. \n \nFive O/Level credit passes in Englis h Language, \nMathematics and any three Arts, Science or \nSocial Sciences. Social Studies and Civic \nEducation are also accepted. \n \nEnglish Language and any three \nArts, Science or Social Sciences. \n \n\n5 \n \n** DE CANDIDATES MUST SATISFY ALL O/LEVEL REQUIREMENTS. \n \n\uf0b7 LINGUISTICS/\nYORUBA \n \n \n \n \n \n \n\uf0b7 CHINESE \ni. Very good passes in three JUPEB/A\u2019 Level \nsubjects in Yoruba/I gbo and any two of History, \nCRS/IRS, French, Government, Music, Visual \nArts and Literature-in-English. \n \nii. NCE (Merit) in two subjects to include a Nigerian \nLanguage. \n \nNO DIRECT ENTRY \nFive O/Level credit passes in English Language, \nMathematics and any three A rts, Science or \nSocial Sciences. Social Studies and Civic \nEducation are also accepted. \n \n \n \n \nFive O/Level credit passes in English Language, \nMathematics and any three Arts, Science or \nSocial Sciences. Social Studies and Civic \nEducation are also accepted. \n \nEnglish Language and any three \nArts, Science or Social Sciences. \n \n \n \n \n \n \nEnglish Language and any three \nArts, Science or Social Sciences. \n\uf0b7 LINGUISTICS i. Three Advanced level passes in GCE or its \nequivalent including any Language. \nii. NCE (minimum of Merit) or Diplom a in any \nNigerian/African/Asian/European Language \nStudies, Communication Arts, Law, Mass \nCommunication, Journalism (minimum of Lower \nCredit). \nFive O/Level credit passes in English Language, \nMathematics, a European/Asian/African/Nigerian \nLanguage and any t wo Arts, Science or Social \nSciences. Social Studies and Civic Education \nare also accepted. \nEnglish Language and any two Arts \nsubjects including any Nigerian/ \nAfrican/Asian/European Language, \nCRS, IRS, Literature-in-English, \nHistory, Government, and other \nsubjects. \nPHILOSOPHY Very good passes in three (3) JUPEB/A' Level \nsubjects: Any three (3) of Literature -in-English, \nIgbo/Yoruba, CRS/IRS, French, History, Economics, \nGovernment, Chemistry, Physics, Biology, \nGeography, but at least one Arts subject. \nFive O/level credit passes in English Language, \nMathematics, one Art and any two Arts, Social \nSciences and Science. Civic Education is also \naccepted.  \nEnglish Language, one Arts and \nany two Arts, Social Sciences or \nScience. \nCHRISTIAN \nRELIGIOUS \nSTUDIES \ni. Passes at t he GCE A/Level or its equivalents. \nOne of the A/Level subjects should be CRS. \nii. NCE with credit or merit in CRS. \nFive O/level Credit passes in English Language, \nMathematics, CRS and any other two subjects. \nEnglish Language, CRS and any \ntwo (2) from Literatur e-in-English, \nHistory, Government, French, \nYoruba, Igbo, Hausa, Visual Arts, \nEconomics and Commerce. \nISLAMIC STUDIES i. Passes at the GCE A/Level or its equivalents. \nOne of the A/Level subjects should be Islamic \nStudies.  \nii. NCE with credit or merit in Islamic Studies. \nFive O/level Credit passes in English Language, \nMathematics, Islamic Studies and any other two \nsubjects \nEnglish Language, Islamic Studies \nand any two from Literature -in-\nEnglish, History, Government, \nFrench, Yoruba, Igbo, Visual Arts, \nEconomics and Commerce. \n\n6 \n \n \nFACULTY OF BASIC MEDICAL SCIENCES \nDEPARTMENT DIRECT ENTRY REQUIREMENTS UTME REQUIREMENTS UTME SUBJECTS \nPHARMACOLOGY i. JUPEB/A' Level  passes in Physics, Chemistry, \nand Biology. \nii. B.Sc. Degree   (First Class/Second Class  \nUpper) in Medical related fields \nFive O/Level credit passes in English Language, \nMathematics, Biology, Chemistry and Physics. \nEnglish Language, Biology, \nChemistry and Physics. \nPHYSIOLOGY i. JUPEB/A' Level  passes in Physics, Chemi stry, \nBiology. \nii. B.Sc. Degree  (First Class/Second Class  \nUpper) in Medical related fields \nFive O/Level credit passes in English Language, \nMathematics, Biology, Chemistry and Physics. \nEnglish Language, Biology, \nChemistry and Physics. \nMEDICAL \nLABORATORY \nSCIENCE \ni.  JUPEB/A\u2019 L evel  passes  in  Physics,  \nChemistry  and Biology \nii. B.Sc. Degree  ( First Class/Second Class  \nUpper) in Medical related fields \nFive O/Level credit passes in English Language, \nMathematics, Biology, Chemistry and Physics. \nEnglish Language, Biolo gy, \nChemistry and Physics. \n** DE CANDIDATES MUST SATISFY ALL O/LEVEL REQUIREMENTS. \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n\n7 \n \nFACULTY OF CLINICAL SCIENCES \nDEPARTMENT DIRECT ENTRY REQUIREMENTS UTME REQUIREMENTS UTME SUBJECTS \nANATOMY Physics, Chemistry, Biology (or Zoology) at A - \nLevel/JUPEB with a minimum of credit pass in five \nSSCE UTME subjects.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 5076, "end_char_idx": 9989, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "00957c13-01fd-438c-ad79-3b2d0c036f8e": {"__data__": {"id_": "00957c13-01fd-438c-ad79-3b2d0c036f8e", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "1", "file_name": "unilag_2024-2025_Admission_Requirements.pdf", "file_path": "/home/prechy/dev/edu-chatbot/data/unilag_2024-2025_Admission_Requirements.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 527929, "creation_date": "2025-07-31", "last_modified_date": "2025-07-31", "source_type": "file", "page_count": 27, "edubot_metadata": {"document_id": "90c4e014-